{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "In multimodal communication, agents have to coordinate heterogeneous modalities and encode various types of information into messages.",
    "A possible solution is to use separate channels to communicate specific modalities, while agents must decide on the right channel to communicate and merge data from different channels.",
    "A more efficient way is to learn a joint representation of multimodal observations and communicate on one channel.",
    "Due to the progress of Multimodal machine learning [111], we can bring ideas from this area to equip agents with the ability to create a single representation of multimodal data.",
    "Nevertheless, it is unclear how the solutions from Multimodal machine learning can be extended to multi-agent reinforcement learning."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Due to the progress of Multimodal machine learning [111], we can bring ideas from this area to equip agents with the ability to create a single representation of multimodal data."
  ]
}